    3x-7&= (3x-2)A+(x+1)B\tag*{\textbf{(M1)}}
\end{align*}3x−7​=(3x−2)A+(x+1)B​(M1)​Next expand the R.H.S. and then collect together the coefficients ofxxxand the constant3x−7=3Ax−2A+Bx+B3x−7=(3A+B)x−2A+B\begin{align*}
    3x-7&=3Ax-2A+Bx+B\\[6pt]
    3x-7&=(3A+B)x-2A+B
\end{align*}3x−73x−7​=3Ax−2A+Bx+B=(3A+B)x−2A+B​We can now equate the coefficients ofxxxand the constant term, to form two equations3A+B=3−2A+B=−7\begin{align*}
    3A+B&=3\\[6pt]
    -2A+B&=-7
\end{align*}3A+B−2A+B​=3=−7​Subtracting the two equations gives5A=10A=2\begin{align*}
    5A&=10\\[6pt]
    A&=2
\end{align*}5AA​=10=2​And3(2)+B=3B=−3\begin{align*}
    3(2)+B&=3\\[6pt]
    B&=-3\\[6pt]
\end{align*}3(2)+BB​=3=−3​Hence we have3x−73x2+x−2=2x+1−33x−2=2x+1+(−33x−2)[In the form required]\begin{align*}
    \dfrac{3x-7}{3x^2+x-2}&=\dfrac{2}{x+1}-\dfrac{3}{3x-2}\\[8pt]
